│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (pet photos and other images)
│
└── data/
    ├── users.txt
    ├── pets.txt
    ├── applications.txt
    ├── favorites.txt
    ├── messages.txt
    ├── adoption_history.txt
    └── shelters.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python application file that contains the web server logic, routing for all pages, data handling (reading/writing to text files), and business logic for the PetAdoptionCenter application. Since the application is not highly complex, consolidating backend code here ensures maintainability and simplicity.

- requirements.txt
  Lists Python dependencies required to run the application (e.g., Flask or other web frameworks).

- README.md
  Documentation file describing the project, setup instructions, and usage.

- templates/
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the web pages, each corresponding to one of the ten pages defined in the requirements. These templates will use templating syntax (e.g., Jinja2 if Flask is used) to dynamically render data.

  - dashboard.html: Dashboard page with featured pets and navigation.
  - pet_listings.html: Page to browse and filter available pets.
  - pet_details.html: Detailed view of a selected pet.
  - add_pet.html: Form page for shelter admins to add new pets.
  - adoption_application.html: Form for users to submit adoption applications.
  - my_applications.html: Displays user's submitted applications.
  - favorites.html: Shows user's favorite pets.
  - messages.html: Messaging interface between users and shelters.
  - user_profile.html: User profile view and edit page.
  - admin_panel.html: Admin interface for managing pets and applications.

- static/
  Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets, JavaScript files, and images.

  - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., navigation buttons, form validation).
  - images/: Folder to store pet photos and other relevant images.

- data/
  Stores all application data in text files as specified, using pipe-delimited format.

  - users.txt: User account information.
  - pets.txt: Pet listings data.
  - applications.txt: Adoption application records.
  - favorites.txt: User favorite pets.
  - messages.txt: Messages between users and shelters.
  - adoption_history.txt: Records of completed adoptions.
  - shelters.txt: Shelter information.
```
This structure cleanly separates backend logic, frontend templates, static resources, and data storage, aligning with the project requirements and ensuring maintainability and scalability."

